	h2 Husky ride across lake inari
	.story The next morning, Ellis and I took a husky ride across Lake Inari. The lake is frozen solid in the thick of the winter. The huskies were eager for the morning run and were tugging hard on the sled. With six huskies to a sled each, we rode in single file. Slowing the huskies down was done by stepping on a primitive metal saw that digs into the ground. Earlier, a snowmobile has dragged a sled laden with weight across the lake. This compacts the snow while created a track. The huskies were fast and the cold morning air swept past our faces. Occasionally, a husky will swipe its mouth across the snow at the side to quench its thirst all the while running.
