	.story Ellis planned for this shot and brought her floral dress. She shared the idea she had in mind and I helped with the execution. We looked around for a good scenery and set up the camera. The action began when she took off her jacket and we worked quickly to get the pose and angle. She said the feeling was indescribable as the cold invades her immediately. This shot was taken by the remote trigger in my hand when I brought the jacket back to her.
