	.story Porvoo was treacherous to get around. It was smaller town and some paths are not de-iced often enough. We wanted to get down to river side but the path was frozen. When a patch of snow has been stepped on, that patch compacts into ice and becomes very slippery. On this path, you can feel yourself sliding off as when the ground has a slight gradient. Normal shoe simply has no grip. I watched as Ellis slid away from me screaming "Dear dear dear save me!" I burst out laughing at the scene. We eventually found another way down. And yes, I did save my wife.
